rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Gitoid](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid), stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects). A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid

A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: configures
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is a configuration applied to each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sensor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded from a physical sensor, such as a thermometer reading or biometric device.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasSpecification
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a specification for the `from` Element (`from` hasSpecification `to`), during a LifecycleScopeType period.
A buildType is a hint that is used to indicate the toolchain, platform, or infrastructure that the build was invoked on.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when the type does not match any of the other options.
A substitute for a URI.
Identifies an external Element used within a Document but defined external to that Document.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDistributionArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is distributed as an artifact in each Element `to` (e.g. an RPM or archive file).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: requirement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element provides a requirement needed as input for another Element
Specifies an Extension characterization of some aspect of an Element.
The version of the SPDX License List used in the license expression.
Points to a resource outside the scope of the SPDX-3.0 content that provides additional characteristics of an Element.
Specifies the algorithm used for calculating the hash value.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 384, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: complete
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known to be exhaustive.
Indicates whether a relationship is known to be complete, incomplete, or if no assertion is made with respect to relationship completeness.
Describes the type of annotation.
Describes one a profile which the creator of this ElementCollection intends to conform to.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deployed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: in addition to being supported by the supplier, the software is known to have been deployed and is in use. For a software as a service provider, this implies the software is now available as a service.
A probability score between 0 and 1 of a vulnerability being exploited.
Indicates the amount of energy consumption incurred by an AI model.
Specifies the CVSS qualitative severity rating of a vulnerability in relation to a piece of software.
Records any relevant background information or additional comments about the origin of the package.
Describes the preprocessing steps that were applied to the raw data to create the given dataset.
Identifies the download Uniform Resource Identifier for the package at the time that the document was created.
Provides a License author's preferred text to indicate that a file is covered by the License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: crystalsKyber
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Kyber](https://pq-crystals.org/kyber/)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The second-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: analyzed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through analysis of artifacts (e.g., executables, packages, containers, and virtual machine images) after its build. Such analysis generally requires a variety of heuristics. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as a "3rd party" SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cpe22
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Platform Enumeration Specification 2.2](https://cpe.mitre.org/files/cpe-specification_2.2.pdf)
Indicates whether the system can perform a decision or action without human involvement or guidance.
Indicates the type of support that is associated with an artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: limitedSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the artifact has been released, and there is limited support available from the supplier. There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.
Specifies the SSVC decision type.
A mathematical algorithm that maps data of arbitrary size to a bit string.
Provides information about the type of an SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exportControlAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a export control assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during the execution phase of an element.
Specifies until when the artifact can be used before its usage needs to be reassessed.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dataset
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Dataset profile specification
Availability of dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is of a type not included in this list.
Describes the type of the given dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: none
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is 0.0

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasStaticLink
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element statically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Defines the end of a range.
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this license or exception identifier was deprecated.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: serious
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The highest level of risk posed by an AI system.
Enumeration of the valid profiles.
A canonical, unique, immutable identifier of the artifact content, that may be used for verifying its identity and/or integrity.
Categories of confidentiality level.
